# Cigar Society — Project Rules

## Project Overview
Premium cigar lounge website for **Cigar Society, LLC** in Pharr, TX.
Stack: React 18 · Vite · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · shadcn/ui · Supabase · React Router v6

## GitHub Workflow (MANDATORY)
- Always read `GUIDES/GITHUB_ISSUES_GUIDE.md` before making any code changes.
- **Every task requires a GitHub Issue.** Create an issue automatically for the task unless the user explicitly opts out.
- After work: **close the issue** when acceptance criteria are clearly met; **otherwise ask** the user whether to close or update the issue.
- Branch naming: `feat/issue-ID-short-description` or `fix/issue-ID-short-description`
- If you are using a fixed working branch (e.g. `Phase-2`) instead, do not create new branches unless asked; still use `[#ISSUE_ID]` in commits **after the user approves** commit/sync.
- **Do not commit or push without explicit user approval** for that action. **Never commit to or push `main`** from agent work.
- Commit format: `[#ISSUE_ID] Commit message`
- PR creation/merge to `main` is manual unless the user explicitly instructs otherwise.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` types unless absolutely unavoidable
- Functional components only — no class components
- Use named exports for components (not default exports on inline functions)
- File naming: `PascalCase.tsx` for components, `camelCase.ts` for utilities/hooks
- Use `@/` path aliases (e.g. `@/components/`, `@/lib/`)
- Prefer `const` over `let`; avoid `var`

## UI / Styling
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/` — do not reinvent primitives
- Tailwind for all styling — no inline `style` props except for dynamic values
- Use CSS custom properties defined in `index.css` for brand colors (do not hardcode hex values)
- Responsive-first: mobile → tablet → desktop
- Animations: use `tailwindcss-animate` classes; keep them subtle
- Do not edit files inside `src/components/ui/` directly — they are shadcn primitives

